      "writtenOn": "2019-09-12T02:41:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "drive-by: i don\u0027t know if your `k, def[k]` has verifiably restricted alphabet, but i\u0027d use bullerproof yet shorter code:\n\n```\nfor k :\u003d range sortedKeys {\n  h.Write([]byte{fmt.Sprintf(\"%08x\", len(k)})\n  h.Write(k)\n  h.Write([]byte{fmt.Sprintf(\"%08x\", len(def[k])})\n  h.Write(def[k])\n}\n\n*change 8 to 16 if you want to support \u003e2GiB long strings.\nFor extra performance, fmt.Sprintf and use something like encoding/binary package.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 59,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 59,
        "endChar": 18
      },
      "revId": "9854702e2d0a7e4107d7597631bee278b574cd44",
