      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027ve diverged a little from some of what I think the comments above are noting, so please let me know how it looks to you. In particular, we don\u0027t generate the pairs as a separate vector at all, which saves a traversal and allocation we don\u0027t need.\n\n*Note in L116 of gtest.go, if we store the base test variant separately, we can skip walking that bit too.",
      "parentUuid": "acf863a0_9d5eb7ea",
      "revId": "9854702e2d0a7e4107d7597631bee278b574cd44",
