      "writtenOn": "2019-09-19T22:36:46Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "i think we need to use https://godoc.org/strings#ToValidUTF8 here, to get a valid string\n\nbut after that, we still need to convert to valid Markdown. The text should be wrapped with `` and angle brackets converted to \u0026gt; and \u0026lt;. Maybe extract it to function in luci/common, since it is sounds generally useful (in separate CL, and then rebase this CL on top of that one)",
