        "id": 1134874
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-09-20T05:11:11Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It looks like\n1) GTest output wants to be wrapped as a code block or span, neither of which should escape angle brackets, and\n2) %q (which is how we discussed outputting the data here in order to preserve the non-UTF8 substrings) already Go-escapes the string, so if we want to render the GTest output nicely we probably actually want to /undo/ some of the whitespace escaping (e.g. for \\n and \\t), and then wrap as a code block.\n\nFor other kinds of output that wouldn\u0027t get treated as code blocks and spans we /would/ want to escape the angle brackets.\n\nWDYT about deciding how to process the strings for GTest output here, and then refactoring out the generalizable parts for Markdown processing later?",
      "parentUuid": "71ca5b18_678583a8",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 128,
