      "message": "\u003e It looks like\n\u003e 1) GTest output wants to be wrapped as a code block or span, neither of which should escape angle brackets, and\n\ni see\n\n\u003e 2) %q (which is how we discussed outputting the data here in order to preserve the non-UTF8 substrings) already Go-escapes the string, so if we want to render the GTest output nicely we probably actually want to /undo/ some of the whitespace escaping (e.g. for \\n and \\t), and then wrap as a code block.\n\nok, then let\u0027s use ToValidUTF8 for now. We can make it more sophisticated later.\n\n\u003e For other kinds of output that wouldn\u0027t get treated as code blocks and spans we /would/ want to escape the angle brackets.\n\u003e \n\u003e WDYT about deciding how to process the strings for GTest output here, and then refactoring out the generalizable parts for Markdown processing later?\n\nok",
